At least eleven people, including three children, were killed in a bus crash on Satansnek, near Ngcobo in the Eastern Cape on Wednesday. It is reported that the bus, which was carrying 60 people, had been travelling from Gauteng to Mthatha when itÂ overturned at a bridge between Ngcobo and Elliot. Eastern Cape health department spokesperson Sizwe Kupelo said mechanical extraction equipment had to be used to open sections of the bus, to assist the passengers and three helicopters ferried survivors to hospital. Kupelo indicated that several people had been transported to hospital for further treatment. -TNA Reporter